          "content": "To solve the expression `((3 - 3 - -3 + -2) + (8 - 2 + -8 - -6))`, we will break it down into two parts corresponding to the parentheses.\n\n**Part 1: `(3 - 3 - -3 + -2)`**\n\n1.  Start with `3 - 3`:\n    $3 - 3 = 0$\n2.  Next, subtract `-3` (which is equivalent to adding 3):\n    $0 - (-3) = 0 + 3 = 3$\n3.  Finally, add `-2` (which is equivalent to subtracting 2):\n    $3 + (-2) = 3 - 2 = 1$\n\nSo, the first part equals **1**.\n\n**Part 2: `(8 - 2 + -8 - -6)`**\n\n1.  Start with `8 - 2`:\n    $8 - 2 = 6$\n2.  Next, add `-8` (which is equivalent to subtracting 8):\n    $6 + (-8) = 6 - 8 = -2$\n3.  Finally, subtract `-6` (which is equivalent to adding 6):\n    $-2 - (-6) = -2 + 6 = 4$\n\nSo, the second part equals **4**.",
